Brian T. Olsavsky 

		
		SVP and CFO, 

	
		 Amazon.com, Inc. 	

 
Last Updated: 07/05/2017 



Executive Summary
Olsavsky is Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Amazon.com, since 2015. Most recently he served as VP of Finance for Amazon’s Global Consumer Business, a position he assumed in 2012. He has been with the company since 2002, when he joined as Vice President of Finance, Global Operations, and subsequently was named 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Olsavsky is a native of Hershey, Pennsylvania.
He currently resides in Seattle. 
Current Focus

Strengthen foothold in Middle East: In July 2017, Amazon completed the acquisition of a Dubai-based e-commerce giant Souq.com for about $580 million, Zacks reported. The companies said that they have taken the “fi 
Key Challenges

"Race to Zero" strategy at AWS: Business Insider reported in  2015, "With [Amazon Web Services] contributing so much to Amazon's newfound profits, will the company keep cutting prices in what the 
Biographical Highlights

Born circa 1963.
Olsavsky earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Mechanical Engineering from Penn State University in 1985. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Member, Alumni Board, Tepper School of Business, Carnegie Mellon University
Member, Board of Trustees, Seattle BioMed 
 





